<subSubSection id="0FC96579FFF489707D9DA00DB887FF4F" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="description">
<paragraph id="476C36F2FFF489707D9DA00DBB28FF1C" blockId="34.[151,1436,552,1275]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFF489707D9DA00DBB0CFE75" bold="true" box="[151,303,552,578]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Description.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="23424B03FFF489707C3DA00CBBC5FE74" author="Distant, W. L." box="[311,486,553,579]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refId="ref55895" refString="Distant, W. L. (1908) Homoptera. Rhynchota vol. 4. The Fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma. Taylor and Francis, London, xv + 501 pp." type="book" year="1908">Distant (1908)</bibRefCitation>
: “Vertex about as long as breadth between eyes and almost as long as pronotum and scutellum united, not angulated in front of eyes, the lateral margins continuous from eyes to apex; face broad between the eyes, angularly narrowed anteriorly; pronotum short, considerably shorter than vertex, with four central ridges, the lateral margins sinuate, anterior and posterior margins nearly straight, the latter only slightly concavely sinuate; scutellum discally foveate; legs moderately short, posterior tibia not foliaceously dilated, outwardly somewhat strongly spinose; forewings short, more or less granulose, apices broadly rounded.”
</paragraph>
